<TEXT>
<P>
Floods and landslides in four days of heavy rain have killed 24 people and 
injured 26 others on Japan's southernmost main island of Kyushu, the National 
Police Agency said Tuesday. Three others were missing. Weather officials said 
22.4 inches of rain fell in Kumamoto between Friday and 6 a.m. Tuesday. 
