<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: IRWINDALE TO PAY FORMER CONSULTANT $1.28 
MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Irwindale City Council has agreed to pay former redevelopment consultant 
Fred Lyte $1.28 million to end a lengthy legal battle stemming from his firing 
in December, 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Lyte was let go when city officials decided that his contract, which gave Lyte 
3% of the building permit fees garnered from the city's redevelopment zone, was 
too generous. 
</P>
<P>
The city later sued Lyte for $2 million, claiming he had violated his contract 
by recommending projects in which he had a financial interest. 
</P>
<P>
Lyte denied that and countersued for $1.4 million in back pay. The decision to 
settle out of court was, according to city council members, an attempt to save 
legal fees, for which the city already had spent $500,000, not an admission of 
guilt. 
</P>
<P>
Lyte said that he was pleased and added: "They paid me what they owed me." 
</P>
</TEXT>
