<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mario Vazquez Rana, president of Pan American Sports Organization, said that 
U.S. television coverage of the 1991 Pan American games in Cuba could be 
arranged through Mexico or Canada. 
</P>
<P>
Vazquez Rana was reacting to a decision by a U.S. federal judge last Friday to 
uphold a U.S. government ban on plans by ABC to televise the games. 
</P>
<P>
The United States said the planned ABC coverage, which would have involved 
payments to Cuba, contravened a U.S. trade embargo imposed in 1961. 
</P>
</TEXT>
