<P>
Toyota Model Passes a Milestone: Toyota Motor Corp. said its Corolla has passed 
Ford's Model-T to become the second best-selling car in history. 
</P>
<P>
A total of 15,040,200 Corollas were made in the 23 years and six months ended 
June 30. That tops the 15,007,033 Model-T cars made by Ford Motor Co. between 
1908 and 1927. But Toyota acknowledges the Volkswagen Beetle as the 
best-selling vehicle of all time, with 20,751,070 Beetles produced since it was 
introduced in 1938. 
</P>
