<P>
Pickens Vows to Hike Koito Stake: Texas oilman T. Boone Pickens Jr. said he 
will move quickly to boost his stake in Koito Manufacturing Co. to 33% from 
26%, despite another defeat of his attempt to gain seats on the board of the 
Japanese auto parts maker. Pickens, who lost his bid to secure four board seats 
at Koito's annual stockholders meeting in Tokyo last week, said he plans to buy 
more Koito stock that could cost him an additional $160 million at about $20 a 
share. By increasing his stake to 33%, Pickens said he would, under Japanese 
law, be allowed participate in decisions made by management. 
