<TEXT>
<P>
Ruling on Drug: The Illinois Supreme Court ruled that companies that 
manufactured the suspected cancer-causing drug DES cannot be forced to pay 
damages to "DES daughters" who do not know what company manufactured the DES 
their mothers took. Justices ruled in the case of a Chicago woman who 
contracted cervical cancer and sued Indianapolis-based Eli Lilly &amp; Co. and 
several other makers of the controversial drug diethlystilbestrol, a synthetic 
female hormone. Studies show daughters of pregnant women who often took the 
drug to prevent miscarriage from the 1940s to the 1960s had a higher incidence 
of cervical cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
