<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIREMAN'S FUND SUES IRVINE'S WESPERCORP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fireman's Fund Insurance Co. on Tuesday filed a $485,000 breach-of-contract 
lawsuit against Wespercorp, an Irvine computer parts company, Wespercorp 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
In a suit filed in Orange County Superior Court in Santa Ana, Fireman's Fund is 
seeking to recover funds that it paid to Citizens Utilities Co. in Stamford, 
Conn., in November, 1986. The payments were made in settlement of a dispute 
related to a contract in which Wespercorp was to provide billing systems to 
Citizens Utilities. 
</P>
<P>
Wespercorp indemnified the payments by Fireman's Fund. But when Fireman's Fund 
asked for repayment in 1989, Wespercorp said it did not have the cash to 
satisfy the obligation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
