International Airport, protesting the loss of jobs at the airport when a new 
company took over cleaning services and did not rehire all the janitorial 
workers. ; Photo, (A2) Protesting for Jobs: Janitors picketed Tuesday at San 
Diego International Airport in protest of the loss of jobs that occurred when a 
new cleaning services contractor took over at the airport Sunday. The union 
claims the company is "anti-worker, anti-union." VINCE COMPAGNONE / Los Angeles 
